  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A model revision was issued on 2025-11-14 to update turbulence closure coefficients; the primary experimental benchmark dataset carries a dataVintage of 2025-10-22, predating that revision by 23 days. The assessment narrative argues the turbulence-coefficient change was 'not material' to the benchmark dataset's relevance, but no formal re-validation against the revised model build was performed. This constitutes a stale-input-data weakness (W-EP-03). Decision recorded as Accepted pending formal re-validation.",
